sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    %% Flow 1: Notebook Creation and Ingress Setup
    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over User,ODHCtrl: Flow 1: Notebook Creation and Ingress Setup

        participant User as User<br/>(kubectl/Dashboard)
        participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        participant ODHWebhook as ODH Mutating Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
        participant KFCtrl as KF Notebook Controller<br/>8081/TCP health
        participant ODHCtrl as ODH Notebook Controller<br/>8080/TCP metrics

        User->>K8sAPI: POST Notebook CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (user)
        K8sAPI->>ODHWebhook: Admission Review<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS (serving cert)
        ODHWebhook->>K8sAPI: GET ImageStream<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA token
        K8sAPI-->>ODHWebhook: ImageStream resolved
        Note over ODHWebhook: Injects kube-rbac-proxy sidecar,<br/>CA bundles, Elyra secrets,<br/>Feast config, MLflow env vars
        ODHWebhook-->>K8sAPI: Mutated Notebook CR
        K8sAPI-->>User: Notebook created

        K8sAPI->>KFCtrl: Watch event (Notebook)
        KFCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA token
        KFCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ClusterIP Service<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA token

        K8sAPI->>ODHCtrl: Watch event (Notebook)
        ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute (nb-{ns}-{name})<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA token
        ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA token
        ODHCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ReferenceGrant<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA token
    end

    %% Flow 2: Notebook Access with kube-rbac-proxy
    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Browser,NotebookPod: Flow 2: Notebook Access with kube-rbac-proxy

        participant Browser as User Browser
        participant Gateway as Platform Gateway<br/>(data-science-gateway)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
        participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
        participant NotebookPod as Notebook Container<br/>8888/TCP HTTP

        Browser->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}/<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Platform OAuth/OIDC
        Gateway->>KRBP: Forward via HTTPRoute<br/>HTTPS/8443 TLS (serving cert)<br/>Auth: Gateway-forwarded identity
        KRBP->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/6443 TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: SA token
        K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Allowed/Denied
        KRBP->>NotebookPod: Proxy request<br/>HTTP/8888 localhost (127.0.0.1)<br/>Headers: X-Auth-Request-User/Groups
        NotebookPod-->>KRBP: Response
        KRBP-->>Gateway: Response (HTTPS)
        Gateway-->>Browser: Response (HTTPS)
    end

    %% Flow 3: Idle Notebook Culling
    rect rgb(245, 255, 230)
        Note over CullingCtrl,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Idle Notebook Culling

        participant CullingCtrl as Culling Controller

        loop Every IDLENESS_CHECK_PERIOD minutes
            CullingCtrl->>NotebookPod: GET /api/kernels<br/>HTTP/8888 (in-cluster DNS)<br/>Auth: None
            NotebookPod-->>CullingCtrl: Kernel activity timestamps
            CullingCtrl->>NotebookPod: GET /api/terminals<br/>HTTP/8888 (in-cluster DNS)<br/>Auth: None
            NotebookPod-->>CullingCtrl: Terminal activity timestamps
        end

        Note over CullingCtrl: If idle > CULL_IDLE_TIME (default 1440m)
        CullingCtrl->>K8sAPI: PATCH annotation<br/>kubeflow-resource-stopped<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA token
        KFCtrl->>K8sAPI: Scale StatefulSet to 0<br/>HTTPS/6443 SA token
    end
